<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 1:38PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Crisp
County through 215 PM EDT...
At 138 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Warwick, or 12 miles
northwest of Ashburn. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Arabi and Fort Early.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
